# Architecture plan for Issue #129: Put faction tallies above the chat feed in mobile order

## Module structure, file organization, shared types
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` defines the TLHN network page section markup in semantic order: countdown, live faction tallies, unified chat feed, composer, and lower page sections.
- `frontend/src/styles.css` owns the Tailwind component-layer layout rules, including mobile-only `order` values for `.tlhn-network-layout` children and the desktop reset at `@media (min-width: 640px)`.
- `shared/src/*`, `backend/src/*`, database migrations, and API types are out of scope because this is a responsive presentation-only change.

## Dependencies between issues
- Issue #129 has no blocking dependencies.
- It adjusts mobile ordering introduced by earlier layout work: countdown remains first, tallies should be second, feed third, composer fourth. Desktop order must continue to reset at `min-width: 640px`.

## Key design decisions
- Implement the fix only in CSS by changing mobile `order` assignments: `.tlhn-network-tallies { order: 2; }` and `.tlhn-network-feed-section { order: 3; }`.
- Preserve DOM order, React components, ARIA labels, feed state handling, chat scrolling, and desktop layout behavior.
- Validate with the frontend typecheck/build or the root build to ensure Tailwind class processing still succeeds.
